annotationA: ATP binding cassette subfamily B member 7 (ABCB7) is a transporter that likely dimerizes to form a functional transporter. ABCB7 may act in the mitochondria to transport substrates necessary for the maturation of ICS proteins, which are involved in iron homeostasis
annotationB: NADPH-dependent diflavin oxidoreductase 1; Component of the cytosolic iron-sulfur (Fe-S) protein assembly (CIA) machinery. Required for the maturation of extramitochondrial Fe-S proteins. Part of an electron transfer chain functioning in an early step of cytosolic Fe-S biogenesis. Transfers electrons from NADPH to the Fe-S cluster of the anamorsin/DRE2 homolog; Belongs to the NADPH-dependent diflavin oxidoreductase NDOR1 family
